<br>
This morning around 3:00am I was on a pick up raid. in KC. The mob : VS.  The item: Wizard Epic item.<br>
<br>
Their was no one true guild, it was a guy (XXXXXX) shouting, &quot;hey if you want to kill VS meet at DL Zone Line.&quot; <br>
<br>
So I meet one of the other 20 people their and join the group that (XXXXXX) is in. The reason im leaving his name blank, is explained later.<br>
<br>
Before the groups are formed it was explain that the loot will be rolled for. All goes well we go into the prep room. We all spell up each other.<br>
<br>
Let me go on to say that the wizards that were with us had their epic piece, except me and (XXXXXX)&lt;Tears of Fire&gt;. As we all jump down. (XXXXXX) &lt;Tears of Fire&gt;Shouts for the pull here comes VS and BAM hes down in 20 secs. Next thing I see (XXXXXX) &lt;Tears of Fire&gt; runs over to him Loots evertything, leaving me and the others to finish off the protectors.  The fight must have lasted about 3 mins. Was not long at all.<br>
<br>
After the fight (XXXXXX) &lt;Tears of Fire&gt; Shouts in the zone that Rogue leg peices drop and something else (wasnt the wizard epic piece) <br>
<br>
Well asks everyone who wants to roll for the 2 items that drop and we all roll for it. <br>
<br>
After the rolls, (XXXXXX) &lt;Tears of Fire&gt; sends me a tell saying, he is sorry he looted the wizard epic piece, but that he needed it and he was cheated out of it last time due to a bug. <br>
<br>
(XXXXXX) who is in &lt;Tears of Fire&gt; went on to say that that because he lost the staff because of a bug last time, he was entitled to the staff this time. <br>
<br>
Talking to some friends who are guides on differant servers they told me to petition; they said this was called Ninja Looting, and it IS BANNABLE. So i did. What do you know a Guide was on. Guide &quot;Sisten&quot;. <br>
<br>
Sisten was wonderfull enough to take down the information and talk to the other people that were in the group. <br>
<br>
Here is the def. of what Sisten said ninja looting was:<br>
Ninja looting is when a player, disregarding the player, or player who killed a mob, loots an Item that is generally regarded significent valuable from the mob they did not kill. <br>
Also Ninja Looting is also defined as when a member of a group loots an item from a mob he helped killed even tho he is not entitled to the item by rules in place for a particular mob.<br>
<br>
So by this def. does that mean he is able to decied that after what HE AND I needed for our epic (The wizard staff) he is to not roll for the item? He can choose to roll for all items other then the Piece that he needed, when he CLEARLY knew that I also needed it. Thus why he sent me a tell to apologize.<br>
<br>
&lt;Tears of Fire&gt; Is this the type of person you want in your guild? A person who is fair to the point up intill where he gets a valuable item,  but does not allow others in the same GROUP, also RAID. To roll for such an item.<br>
<br>
Is Ninja looting a bannable offense?<br>
<br>
Sisten did what he could do, take down the information and asked me to repetition today at 3pm. I can totally understand where only a GM of the server can make such a deciding  on actions to be taken.<br>
<br>
Im not saying the name of who (XXXXXX) &lt;Tears of Fire&gt; is, because I am going to allow the GM to handle the matter. Ill post an update tommorrow after 3:00pm<br>
<br>
